Package com.pandora.general.objects

Class PandoraTimestep

java.lang.Object
com.pandora.general.objects.PandoraTimestep
public class PandoraTimestep extends Object
The PandoraTimestep class represents a specific time step in the Pandora model, characterized by initial values, start and end times, dimensionality, discharge, volume, terrestrial and upstream sources, and other properties.

This class includes a builder method (builder()) for constructing instances using the Builder pattern.

Version:
0.0.1
Author:
Wim Joost van Hoek

  • Method Details

    • builder

      public static PandoraTimestepBuilder builder()
      Returns a new instance of PandoraTimestepBuilder to facilitate the construction of PandoraTimestep instances using the Builder pattern.

      Example usage: 

      
 PandoraTimestep timestep = PandoraTimestep.builder().y0(initialValues).t0(startTime).tEnd(endTime)
         .dimension(simulationDimension).discharge(dischargeValue).volume(volumeValue)
         .terrestrialSources(terrestrialSourcesArray).upstreamSources(upstreamSourcesArray).build();
      Returns:
      A new instance of PandoraTimestepBuilder.
